What you need to know:

KTDA has already gone to court to stop the implementation of the reforms.Murang’a County has the largest concentration of tea factories in the country.Aall the local elected leaders — apart from Woman Rep Wanjiru Chege and Gatanga MP Nduati Ngugi — skipped the meeting that was attended by 1,300 tea sector stakeholders.The Meru County boss has been telling farmers to resist the changes proposed by his predecessor.